EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to governmental administration; making an
appropriation to City of Hope to establish an outpatient
cancer treatment clinic; establishing the Oncology
Excellence Committee within the Department of Health
and Human Services; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Section 1 of this bill makes an appropriation to City of Hope to establish an
2 outpatient cancer treatment clinic in Clark County. Section 1 requires City of Hope,
3 upon acceptance of the money, to: (1) enter into an affiliation agreement with the
4 Kirk Kerkorian School of Medicine at the University of Nevada, Las Vegas to
5 provide clinical training to students of the Kirk Kerkorian School of Medicine; and
6 (2) prepare and transmit reports to the Interim Finance Committee and the
7 Oncology Excellence Committee within the Department of Health and Human
8 Services created by section 2 of this bill regarding each expenditure made from the
9 money appropriated to City of Hope. Section 2 creates the Oncology Excellence
10 Committee and requires the Committee to: (1) obtain confirmation that City of
11 Hope has entered into the required agreement with the Kirk Kerkorian School of
12 Medicine; and (2) monitor the use of money appropriated to City of Hope to ensure
13 that the money is used only for authorized purposes. Section 3 of this bill provides
14 for the expiration on October 1, 2027, of the provisions creating the Committee.
