THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
2 General Fund to City of Hope the sum of $50,000,000 to establish
3 an outpatient cancer treatment clinic in Clark County.
4 2. The money appropriated by subsection 1 may be used to:
5 (a) Lease office space;
6 (b) Make tenant improvements;
7 (c) Purchase office equipment;
8 (d) Purchase specialized medical equipment; and
9 (e) Pay staff of the treatment clinic.
10 3. Upon acceptance of the money appropriated by subsection 1,
11 City of Hope agrees to:
12 (a) On or before January 1, 2026, enter into an affiliation
13 agreement with the Kirk Kerkorian School of Medicine at the
14 University of Nevada, Las Vegas to provide clinical training to
15 students of the Kirk Kerkorian School of Medicine. The duration of
16 the affiliation agreement must be for not less than 5 years.
17 (b) Prepare and transmit a report to the Interim Finance
18 Committee and the Oncology Excellence Committee created by
19 section 2 of this act, on or before December 18, 2026, that describes
20 each expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection
21 1 from the date on which the money was received by City of Hope
22 through December 1, 2026.
23 (c) Prepare and transmit a final report to the Interim Finance
24 Committee and the Oncology Excellence Committee created by
25 section 2 of this act, on or before September 17, 2027, that describes
26 each expenditure made from the money appropriated by subsection
27 1 from the date on which the money was received by City of Hope
28 through June 30, 2027.
29 (d) Upon request of the Legislative Commission, make available
30 to the Legislative Auditor any of the books, accounts, claims,
31 reports, vouchers or other records of information, confidential or
32 otherwise, of City of Hope, regardless of their form or location, that
33 the Legislative Auditor deems necessary to conduct an audit of the
34 use of the money appropriated pursuant to subsection 1.
35 4. Any remaining balance of the appropriation made by
36 subsection 1 must not be committed for expenditure after June 30,
37 2027, by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
38 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
39 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
40 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
41 September 17, 2027, by either the entity to which the money was
42 appropriated or the entity to which the money was subsequently
