1 granted or transferred, and must be reverted to the State General
2 Fund on or before September 17, 2027.
3 Sec. 2. 1. The Oncology Excellence Committee is hereby
4 created within the Department of Health and Human Services.
5 2. The Committee consists of the following nine members:
6 (a) Seven members appointed by the Governor:
7 (1) One of whom must be selected by the Board of County
8 Commissioners of Clark County;
9 (2) One of whom must be selected by the Dean of the Kirk
10 Kerkorian School of Medicine at the University of Nevada, Las
11 Vegas;
12 (3) One of whom must be selected by the Executive Director
13 of the Office of Economic Development;
14 (4) One of whom must be selected by the Director of the
15 Department of Health and Human Services;
16 (5) Two of whom must be selected by the Governor; and
17 (6) One of whom must be a representative of an organization
18 that advocates on behalf of persons with cancer.
19 (b) One member appointed by the Majority Leader of the
20 Senate.
21 (c) One member appointed by the Speaker of the Assembly.
22 3. The Committee shall:
23 (a) At its first meeting and annually thereafter, elect a Chair
24 from among its members;
25 (b) Meet at the call of the Chair or a majority of its members as
26 necessary, but not to exceed six meetings per year;
27 (c) Obtain confirmation that City of Hope has entered into the
28 agreement required by paragraph (a) of subsection 3 of section 1 of
29 this act, not later than January 1, 2026;
30 (d) Monitor the use of money appropriated to City of Hope
31 pursuant to subsection 1 of section 1 of this act to ensure that the
32 money is used only for the purposes listed in subsection 2 of section
33 1 of this act; and
34 (e) Notify the Fiscal Analysis Division of the Legislative
35 Counsel Bureau if it appears that:
36 (1) City of Hope has not entered into the agreement required
37 by paragraph (a) of subsection 3 of section 1 of this act on or before
38 January 1, 2026.
39 (2) Money appropriated pursuant to subsection 1 of section 1
40 of this act has been used for a purpose other than the purposes listed
41 in subsection 2 of section 1 of this act.
42 4. Each member of the Committee serves without
43 compensation and is not entitled to receive a per diem allowance or
44 travel expenses.
